
[1]annihilate

   ANNI'HILATE, v.t. [L. ad and nihilum, nothing, of ne, not, and hilum, a
   trifle.]

   1. To reduce to nothing; to destroy the existence of.

   No human power can annihilate matter.

   2. To destroy the form or peculiar distinctive properties, so that the
   specific thing no longer exists; as, to annihilate a forest by cutting
   and carrying away the trees, though the timber may still exist; to
   annihilate a house by demolishing the structure.
